---
description: PostgreSQL model patterns (getPool, parameterized SQL, transactions)
globs: src/models/**/*.js
alwaysApply: false
---

## DB model conventions

- Import DB access from `src/config/database.js`:
  - `import { getPool } from '../config/database.js';`
- Do **not** instantiate `new Pool()` in application models.
- Always use parameterized queries (`$1`, `$2`, ...) with params arrays.

## Transactions

Use an explicit client when doing multi-step writes:

```js
const pool = getPool();
const client = await pool.connect();
try {
  await client.query('BEGIN');
  // ... multiple queries ...
  await client.query('COMMIT');
} catch (error) {
  await client.query('ROLLBACK');
  throw error;
} finally {
  client.release();
}
```

## Errors & logging

- Log structured context via `logger.error('...', { error: error.message, stack: error.stack, ...context })`.
- Re-throw the error after logging so controllers can `next(error)`.
